    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A front-page article on April 4 about Arnold Blume, an 81-year-old substitute teacher on Long Island who shares his firsthand knowledge of historical events in class, included an erroneous reference from Mr. Blume to the day in 1945 when he and fellow members of the Army Air Corps assembled for a memorial service for President Franklin D. Roosevelt. The men were in their green dress uniform, not dress blues. (A spokesman for the Air Force, which succeeded the Air Corps, said the dress blues uniform was not introduced to the Air Force until 1949.)</p>
      </block>
